objects.name: Well
objects.description: The origin of a set of wellbores.

objects.name: WellLog
objects.description: A well log is a data type that correlates a particular measurement or multiple measurements in a wellbore against depth and/or time within that wellbore. When plotted visually, well logs are typically long line graphs (called "curves") but may sometimes be discrete points or intervals. This schema object is intended for digital well logs, not raster log files or raster calibration files, but may be used for the latter in the absence of a defined OSDU schema for these use cases.

objects.description: A hole in the ground extending from a point at the earth's surface to the maximum point of penetration.

objects.description: https://schema.osdu.opengroup.org/json/master-data/Wellbore.1.0.0.json

objects.name: AccessControlLIst
objects.description: The access control tags associated with this entity. This structure is included by the SystemProperties \"acl\", which is part of all OSDU records. Not extensible.

objects.name: AccessControlList
objects.description: The access control tags associated with this entity.

objects.name: AcquisitionDate
objects.description: The date that the survey data was acquired on the field.

objects.name: AcquisitionRemark
objects.description: Remarks related to acquisition context which is not the same as Description which is a summary of the work-product-component.

objects.name: ActiveIndicator
objects.description: A flag indicating if the survey is currently active or valid within his lifecycle stage, not necessarily the definitive survey.

objects.name: AgeMax
objects.description: Absolute age, for chronostrat columns, max of  bottom bed (varying)

objects.name: AgeMin
objects.description: Absolute age, for chronostrat columns, min of top bed

objects.name: Area
objects.description: basin, region, field, segment

objects.name: AzimuthReferenceType
objects.description: The North reference of the trajectory used to define the azimuth angular measurement values. For example, True North, Grid North, Magnetic North.

objects.name: BaseDepthMeasuredDepth
objects.description: Measured depth within the wellbore of the LAST surveyed station with recorded data.  If a stored survey has been extrapolated to a deeper depth than the last surveyed station then that is the extrapolated measured depth and not the survey base depth.

objects.name: CalculationMethodType
objects.description: Calculation Method Type used to compute the TVD, X OFFSET, Y OFFSET and DOG LEG SEVERITY values for this Directional Survey. For example, Radius of Curvature, Minimum Curvature, Balanced Tangential, etc.

objects.name: Coordinate
objects.description: The default vertical coordinate reference system used in the vertical measurements for a well or wellbore if absent from input vertical measurements and there is no other recourse for obtaining a valid CRS.

objects.name: CoordinateReferenceSystem
objects.description: Coordinate Reference System defining the Projection of the station EASTING and NORTHING values. If  type is \"Grid North\" and EASTING and NORTHING attributes are stored, clearly identifying their projection is required.

objects.name: DepositionalGeometry
objects.description: Area of validity - lines? Used for geomodelling/gridding specs.

objects.name: WellLog
objects.description: A well log is a data type that correlates a particular measurement or multiple measurements in a wellbore against depth and/or time within that wellbore. When plotted visually, well logs are typically long line graphs (called "curves") but may sometimes be discrete points or intervals. This schema object is intended for digital well logs, not raster log files or raster calibration files, but may be used for the latter in the absence of a defined OSDU schema for these use cases.
